# Requester Read — No Entity Id Echo

## Rule

For website multi-path edit forms, `read` result `values` MUST **not** include the entity identity key (`member`, `messageChannel`, …).

Identity is seeded by the screen via `useShallowForm` `initProps.values` (from the route `id`). Form merge keeps that key across `read` hydration.

## Why

Echoing the id from `read` is redundant and caused drift (template-string / typed-object mistakes). Canonical pattern: Member + MessageChannel requesters.

## Forbidden

```ts
result.setData({
    values: {
        member: member.get("id"), // do not
        name: …
    }
});
```

## Correct

```ts
result.setData({
    values: {
        name: …,
        // identity stays in form initProps only
    }
});
```

Authority: `docs/platforms/backend/contracts/member-domain.md` §9.3, `message-channel-domain.md` §5.

Related select hydrate (enums / entity refs on the same `read`): `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/requester-read-select-hydrate.md`.
